From: Trung Lê <8@tle.id.au>
Subject: Makefile.am: plug two missed CDE_* macro defines surfaced by check-fhs

Sweep with util/check-fhs.sh (Patch0007) over the post-patch source
tree turned up two Makefile.am sites where -DCDE_*_TOP flags were
missing or wrong, causing the legacy fallback paths in headers and
source to silently fire on FHS builds.

1. lib/DtSvc/Makefile.am: libDtSvc_la_CPPFLAGS already passes
   CDE_INSTALLATION_TOP, CDE_DATA_TOP and CDE_CONFIGURATION_TOP, but
   not CDE_LOGFILES_TOP. As a result:

     - lib/DtSvc/DtUtil2/MsgLog.c falls into its
       `#ifdef CDE_LOGFILES_TOP / #else "/var/dt/tmp"` branch and
       opens its log/temp files at /var/dt/tmp.

     - lib/DtSvc/DtEncap/nls.c falls into its
       `#ifndef CDE_LOGFILES_TOP / #define "/var/dt/tmp"` fallback
       and XeSBTempPath() returns paths under /var/dt/tmp.

   With --with-cde-state-dir=/var/lib/cde this is plain wrong; both
   files should track CDE_LOGFILES_TOP.

2. programs/dtspcd/Makefile.am: dtspcd_CFLAGS sets
       -DCDE_CONFIGURATION_TOP=\"${prefix}\"
   which is wrong on every layout, not just FHS -- it pins
   dtspcd's config-dir notion to whatever --prefix is (/usr on
   Fedora, /usr/dt on a Solaris-style build) instead of honoring
   --with-cde-config-dir. Combined with
       include/SPC/spcP.h: SPCD_ENV_CONFIG_DIRECTORY = CDE_CONFIGURATION_TOP "/config"
   dtspcd ends up probing /usr/config/dtspcdenv instead of
   /etc/cde/config/dtspcdenv. (lib/DtSvc/DtEncap/spc-env.c uses the
   same macro but gets the correct value via lib/DtSvc/Makefile.am;
   only dtspcd itself was broken.)

   Looks like a pre-existing upstream typo predating
   --with-cde-config-dir; Patch0008 already touched this file (to
   add CDE_DATA_TOP) without noticing the ${prefix} substitution.

--- a/lib/DtSvc/Makefile.am
+++ b/lib/DtSvc/Makefile.am
@@ -14,7 +14,8 @@
 libDtSvc_la_CPPFLAGS = -I./include -DMULTIBYTE -DNLS16 -I../include \
 	@DT_INCDIR@ -DCDE_INSTALLATION_TOP=\"$(CDE_INSTALLATION_TOP)\" \
 	-DCDE_DATA_TOP=\"$(CDE_DATA_TOP)\" \
-       -DCDE_CONFIGURATION_TOP=\"$(CDE_CONFIGURATION_TOP)\"
+       -DCDE_CONFIGURATION_TOP=\"$(CDE_CONFIGURATION_TOP)\" \
+       -DCDE_LOGFILES_TOP=\"$(CDE_LOGFILES_TOP)\"

 if SOLARIS
 libDtSvc_la_CPPFLAGS += -DNO_REGCOMP
--- a/programs/dtspcd/Makefile.am
+++ b/programs/dtspcd/Makefile.am
@@ -2,7 +2,7 @@ MAITAINERCLEANFILES = Makefile.in

 bin_PROGRAMS = dtspcd

-dtspcd_CFLAGS = -DCDE_CONFIGURATION_TOP=\"${prefix}\" \
+dtspcd_CFLAGS = -DCDE_CONFIGURATION_TOP=\"$(CDE_CONFIGURATION_TOP)\" \
 		-DCDE_INSTALLATION_TOP=\"$(CDE_INSTALLATION_TOP)\" \
 		-DCDE_DATA_TOP=\"$(CDE_DATA_TOP)\" \
 		$(DT_INCDIR)
